cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Function-Tunnel Intelligence (FTI): Elastic Structural Runtime Intelligence for Robust Autonomous Systems"
message: "If you use this repository or its concepts, please cite this work."
type: software

authors:
  - family-names: Tan
    given-names: Sizhe
    affiliation: Independent Researcher

abstract: >-
  Function-Tunnel Intelligence (FTI) introduces an elastic structural runtime
  intelligence paradigm for robust autonomous systems. Instead of requiring
  exact path-following, exact synchronization, or rigid trajectory matching,
  FTI proposes that intelligent systems should remain inside acceptable
  structural function-tunnels. The framework combines Time-Series Curve
  Elastic IR, function-tunnel navigation, behavioral manifold stabilization,
  policy tunnel governance, and structural corridor matching. Applications
  include low-cost drone navigation, robotics, swarm systems, AI runtime
  governance, structural AI coding, and post-LLM control-plane design.

